.TH RDUP-SNAP-HERE.SH 8 "14 Mar 2006" "@PACKAGE_VERSION@" "@PACKAGE_NAME@ utils"

.SH NAME
rdup-snap-here.sh \- dump a filesystem to where this script is located

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rdup-snap-here.sh

.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBrdup-snap-here.sh\fR is a graphical (using zenity)
front-end for `rdup-snap' and `rdup'.
Its main purpose is that it is used as `autorun.sh' on removeable media.
This way you can backup automaticaly when you power on or insert such
media.
.PP
This script will use are hardlink technique to create the backup
.PP
The backup will be stored in the directory where \fBrdup-snap-here.sh\fR is
called from - usually this is in the root of the removeable media.
.PP
The script must be edited to be really usefull - as there is no
way to give it options (when run as `autorun.sh') the directories
to be backed up \fImust\fR be specifed at the top of the script.

.SH FILES
`pwd`/`hostname` is the default location for the backups. That is:
where ever \fBrdup-snap-here.sh\fR is located is taken as the backup
directory.

.SH SEE ALSO
rdup(8) and rdup-snap(8).
